A MPUMALANGA cop and her two accomplices were released on R2000 bail each by the Witbank Magistrates Court on Tuesday for the alleged kidnapping of 13 undocumented immigrants. The cop (56) and her co-accused are facing charges of kidnapping, defeating the ends of justice and extortion. According to Colonel Donald Mdhluli, undocumented people were taken into a police-marked van for hours, where a bribe of R10 000 was demanded. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments They were working at a construction site, where the owner was also contacted to pay. They will appear in court on 1 March.